at|Here the @S9 is the proper signal because it is higher (and therefore louder) than the @S8. |
pg| ***** 103 ***** |


md|0sq,,,sj|

nt|^b@2^z@3Here is another important lesson that we have learned about signaling:

|
pg| ***** 104 ***** |


cs|2|at|^-{ Sometimes a defender is not dealt the spot cards to convey the message that he would 
like. He can only try his best and hope that his partner is able to work out the position. }
^-
|
