nt|^b@2^z@3
We will be considering count and suit preference signals later in this chapter. The study of attitude signals has formed the bulk of this chapter thus far. Here is a reminder of the basic nature of the attitude signal:

|
pg| ***** 471 ***** |


cs|1|at|^-{ Follow suit with or discard a high card to show that you have a critical honor in that suit. 
 Follow suit with or discard a low card to deny that you have a critical honor in that suit. }
^-
|
pg| ***** 472 ***** |


at|The terms encouraging and discouraging are used to describe the 2 flavors of attitude signals. To encourage is to send your partner a positive message about a suit by playing a high card in that suit. To discourage is to send your partner a negative message about a suit by playing a low card in that suit.

|
pg| ***** 473 ***** |


at|3 situations where attitude signals should be used have been considered:

|
pg| ***** 474 ***** |


cs|4|at|^-{ 1. When your partner leads an honor card, you should usually give him an attitude signal. }

|
pg| ***** 475 ***** |


cs|3|at|{ 2. When your partner leads to a trick and the second hand to play appears to be 
 winning that trick, it is usually correct to give your partner an attitude signal. }

|
pg| ***** 476 ***** |


cs|2|at|{ 3. The first discard that a player makes in a suit should be interpreted as an attitude signal. }
^-
|
pg| ***** 477 ***** |


at|Later in this chapter we will see one other situation where attitude signals should be used. 

|
pg| ***** 478 ***** |


nt|^b@2^z@3
We have seen that a defender can signal his attitude with both spot cards and honor cards. Attitude signals with honor cards describe a specific holding:

|
pg| ***** 479 ***** |


Cs|1|at|^-{ An attitude signal of an honor card shows that the player making this signal holds 
 the next lower honor card and that he does not hold the next higher honor card. }

|
pg| ***** 480 ***** |


cs|4|at|{ Attitude signals with honors are useful because they tell your partner a lot about your
 hand, but do not use one of these signals if you need all of your honors for winning tricks! }
^-
|
pg| ***** 481 ***** |


at|The question of when to encourage and when to discourage is not an easy one to answer.

|
pg| ***** 482 ***** |


cs|2|at|^-{ There are no magic formulas to tell you when to encourage and when to discourage. 
 For guidance, consider factors like your own hand, the dummy's hand, and the bidding! }
^-
|
pg| ***** 483 ***** |


at|However, when your partner leads an honor card, there are some fairly reliable guidelines about when you should offer an encouraging attitude signal:

|
pg| ***** 484 ***** |


cs|3|at|^-{ When your partner leads an honor card, encourage if you have a higher honor. }

|
pg| ***** 485 ***** |


cs|1|at|{ Also encourage if you have a lower honor touching the lowest card your partner promised. }
|
pg| ***** 486 ***** |


nt|^b@2^z@3
The last type of attitude signals that we looked at were when the first discard that a defender makes in a suit should be interpreted as such a signal. Here are some tips that will help you to give effective attitude signals when you are discarding:

|
pg| ***** 487 ***** |


cs|4|at|^-{Attitude signals relate to the suit of the signal (not the suit that was led). In most cases
 these suits are the same, but when a discard is an attitude signal they will not be the same! }

|
pg| ***** 488 ***** |


cs|2|at|{ Sometimes you will not be able to afford to discard an encouraging card as an 
 attitude signal because you will need all of your high cards in that suit to win tricks. }

|
pg| ***** 489 ***** |


cs|3|at|{ If you cannot afford to discard an encouraging card from the suit you like, you can
 transmit the same message by discarding discouraging cards in the suits that you don't like. }

|
pg| ***** 490 ***** |


cs|1|at|{ If you want to give a discouraging attitude signal in 2 suits, your first discard should 
 be from the suit that your partner would be more likely to play should he regain the lead. }

|
pg| ***** 491 ***** |


cs|4|at|{ When faced with a choice between encouraging in one suit and discouraging in some
 other suit, an encouraging attitude signal sends a stronger message to your partner. }
^-
|
